<div><h3>MGMT 5786 - Research: Answering Important Management Questions </h3>  <p><hr>This course provides students with the opportunity to conduct applied research on real-world issues related to human behavior in organizations (e.g., managing change, employee motivation). Students will gain an understanding of the methods used in research on organizational behavior and human resources management. Topics covered include problem identification, research design, data collection methods (e.g., experiments, surveys, and interviews), data analysis, and reporting. Student teams will use this knowledge to complete a research project that addresses a problem identified by a client organization.</p>

<p>Counts as Experiential Learning Requirement II for the MBA program or as an elective.</p>

<p>Open to MBA students only.</p>

